I was in Lower Guk the other day. Yes i was in a bad mood, and had already had an argument (stupid as it was) with a wizard about shouting for camp checks. No biggie. He killed me. I admit(ted) that i was wrong. Maybe he'll read this and not hate me for eternity.<br>
<br>
anyways that's not the point.<br>
<br>
I was in a miffy mood. We were pulling the Magus room (where we were camped) the Hand room, and the Lord room, Successfully.<br>
<br>
Wimbus comes. Blue to me. So yeah 36 fits i guess. He takes the Lord room, with a friend of his; some shaman (could be a double boxer: I don't care). So I start just pulling the things in the hall up in the direction of the lord room.<br>
<br>
I use f8 for targeting. Accidentally pulled to 2 spawns next to the lord's throne (lord wasn't up). This is of course via using throwing... so i auto swung to throw at the guys. Whoops. I only wanted one.<br>
<br>
Ran! Stupid mistake on my part. Forgot for a brief second i was a monk. I feign death. I trained Wimbus. I feel like a total ass. <br>
<br>
I bring the other things that aggro'd onto me when i got up to the magus room for my group to dispatch them. Then i run back to wimbus (didn't want to train him with the rest of the junk. Was hoping to bring stuff back and still have time to help him once my group's MT grabbed them.)<br>
<br>
I run back. He's doing fine. I wait for him to finish off the two, just in case.<br>
<br>
But he isn't impressed. What followed was a bunch of rude comments to me: My favourite was &quot;it's people like you that ruin the reputation of FV&quot;. Nothing was said in character from him. So i responded in like terms. Apologised for the accidental train. He didn't/refused to believe me. He sent tells to my group saying that he would never ever group with my guild members again or join my guild. He harrassed me for a good ten minutes about pulling things from the hall as he had the lord room camped. Stay away from my camp! Get out of my camp. &quot;The hall isn't the lord room&quot;: was my response.<br>
<br>
He made my ignore list. <br>
<br>
He left soon after. The lord popped right after that. I took the chance. He never came back. But that too is beside the point.<br>
<br>
My point is basically. People that are looking for someone to RP with. Shouldn't do it with Wimbus. I'm sorry to say. I know i shouldn't have trained him. What i did was wrong. But I did apologise... a couple of times. And I don't feel i owe him anything more than that. He was out of line IMHO.<br>
<br>
Judging from what you folks say he did. I don't think I'm incorrect in that assumption. <br>
<br>
As always there are two sides to any story. And this is my side. Take it or leave it. I don't care.<br>
